{"parse":{"title":"Moses Rischin","pageid":15873429,"revid":824247369,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Moses Rischin</b> (born 1925) is an American <a href=\"/wiki/Jewish\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Jewish\">Jewish</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Historian\" title=\"Historian\">historian</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Author\" title=\"Author\">author</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Lecturer\" title=\"Lecturer\">lecturer</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Editing\" title=\"Editing\">editor</a>, and <a href=\"/wiki/Emeritus_professor\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Emeritus professor\">emeritus professor</a> of history at <a href=\"/wiki/San_Francisco_State_University\" title=\"San Francisco State University\">San Francisco State University</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-MJL_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-MJL-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Lehrhaus_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Lehrhaus-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> He coined the phrase <a href=\"/wiki/New_Mormon_history\" title=\"New Mormon history\">new Mormon history</a> in a 1969 article of the same name.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Sunstone_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Sunstone-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Rischin is from <a href=\"/wiki/New_York_City\" title=\"New York City\">New York City</a>.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (February 2008)\">citation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup> His undergraduate studies were at <a href=\"/wiki/Brooklyn_College\" title=\"Brooklyn College\">Brooklyn College</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/wiki/Harvard_University\" title=\"Harvard University\">Harvard University</a> awarded him a <a href=\"/wiki/PhD\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"PhD\">PhD</a> in 1957.<sup id=\"cite_ref-SFSU_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-SFSU-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> In addition to his professorship, he sits on the board for the <i>Journal of American Ethnic History</i> and on the council of the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=American_Jewish_History_Society&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"American Jewish History Society (page does not exist)\">American Jewish History Society</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Chadwyck_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Chadwyck-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-AJHS_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-AJHS-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> There is an annual lecture given in his honor at the <a href=\"/wiki/Western_Jewish_History_Center\" title=\"Western Jewish History Center\">Western Jewish History Center</a>, where he is director.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Emanueldec05_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Emanueldec05-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> There is a collection of historical essays published in Rischin's honor,<sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> and a supporting character, Meyer Meyer in the <a href=\"/wiki/87th_Precinct\" title=\"87th Precinct\">87th Precinct</a> series, may have been partly modeled after him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Rischin is considered an authority on <a href=\"/wiki/History_of_immigration_to_the_United_States\" title=\"History of immigration to the United States\">American ethnic and immigration history</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-NYT06071993_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-NYT06071993-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup> and a pioneer in the field of <a href=\"/wiki/History_of_the_Jews_in_the_United_States\" title=\"History of the Jews in the United States\">American Jewish history</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-14\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup> Historian <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Selma_Berrol&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Selma Berrol (page does not exist)\">Selma Berrol</a>, however, has challenged the minimal treatment Rischin has given to the tensions between earlier German Jews and later Russian Jews in America.<sup id=\"cite_ref-15\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During the <a href=\"/wiki/Monica_Lewinsky_scandal\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Monica Lewinsky scandal\">Monica Lewinsky scandal</a>, Rischin was a signatory of \"Historians in Defense of the Constitution\" wherein 400 historians criticized efforts to <a href=\"/wiki/Impeachment_of_Bill_Clinton\" title=\"Impeachment of Bill Clinton\">impeach President Bill Clinton</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Salon_16-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Salon-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-WP_17-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-WP-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Books\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Books</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Articles_and_essays\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Articles and essays</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Books\">Books</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Moses_Rischin&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Books\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><i>The Promised City: New York's Jews, 1870-1914</i> (<a href=\"/wiki/Harvard_University_Press\" title=\"Harvard University Press\">Harvard University Press</a>) <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0674715011\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0674715011\">978-0674715011</a></li>\n<li><i>Jews of the American West</i>, with John Livingston (<a href=\"/wiki/Wayne_State_University_Press\" title=\"Wayne State University Press\">Wayne State University Press</a>) <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-8143-2171-2\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-8143-2171-2\">0-8143-2171-2</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Articles_and_essays\">Articles and essays</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Moses_Rischin&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Articles and essays\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>\"The New Mormon History\", <i>The American West</i> 6, March 1969, 49.</li>\n<li>\"The Jewish Experience in America: A View from the West\"</li>\n<li>Foreword to <i>California Jews</i> (2003) Brandeis University Press</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><